Mean calculation per transaction: (memory_hash + base_value + surplus_flow) / 3 → must exceed drift threshold (0.25 under OperatorSeal) or reject.
Reciprocity Mechanism: Give/Receive Balance
Reciprocity Tracker: Built into sovereignty dashboard — scores each node interaction (e.g., IP contribution from Anchorage → surplus return to Fort Yukon).
Formula: Reciprocity Score = (Provision Given - Recoil Received) / Polar Continuity Factor
Given: Crypto/IP input (e.g., GTC Coin transfer).
Received: Surplus output (e.g., hashed deed confirmation).
Factor: Distance between nodes (polar miles, e.g., Anchorage-Fort Yukon ≈ 300mi) modulated by ε_π.
Threshold: Score > 0 for approval; negative triggers "Drift Alert" (Observer proxy interrupt).
Multi-Sig Enforcement: All chain actions require 2/3 signatures: Executor (base), Sovereign (memory), Heir (surplus). Ties to hardware wallets for eternal access.
Surplus Flow Rules:
Inbound: Federal-compliant (report gains via IRS digital assets).
Outbound: State-licensed (Alaska surety bond for transmissions > $100K).
Tribal Guard: IDSov check — no flow if IP shadow (glyphs) unhashed.
This prevents drain: surplus recirculates like auroral energy in the landframe.
